## Testing Expectations

{% if test_strategy == "junit-only" %}
- Prefer plain JUnit tests for business logic
- Use Spring test slices when HTTP, validation, or repository wiring matters
{% elif test_strategy == "junit-and-testcontainers" %}
- Use Testcontainers for database-backed integration tests
- Avoid fake compatibility layers that hide real database behavior
{% else %}
- Cover pure logic with unit tests
- Cover Spring behavior with slice tests
- Reserve end-to-end tests for critical flows only
{% endif %}

## Security Notes

{% if use_auth and auth_method == "jwt" %}
- Protected endpoints expect bearer tokens
- Token parsing belongs in Spring Security configuration, not individual controllers
{% elif use_auth and auth_method == "oauth2" %}
- Resource-server settings, issuer, and scope mapping are security-owned concerns
- Authorization decisions still need tests close to the business use case
{% elif use_auth and auth_method == "api-key" %}
- API key handling should be centralized and auditable
- Do not duplicate header parsing logic across controllers
{% else %}
- If auth is not enabled, document the trust assumptions before exposing endpoints
{% endif %}

## Integration Notes

{% if use_redis %}
- Redis is available for caching or short-lived coordination, not as the primary system of record
{% endif %}
{% if use_kafka %}
- Kafka messages are contracts; changing payload shape is a breaking change unless versioned
{% endif %}
- Repository behavior should be verified against the real database engine where correctness matters
- Migrations, event contracts, and auth changes deserve explicit review attention
